cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper deals with motion planning of networked mobile robots, which is a core topic in robotics. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a control theoretical framework for motion planning, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
3. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper deals with a team of networked mobile robots, which can be considered as a multi-agent system. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses Signal Temporal Logic (STL) and Spatial Temporal Reach and Escape Logic (STREL) to specify the desired motion and communication objectives, which are formal methods used in artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a distributed model predictive control (MPC) approach for computing control strategies, which falls under the domain of distributed computing.
